name: market for water pump operation, diesel | water pump operation, diesel | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/19522/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'water pump operation, diesel', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;'water pump operation, diesel' describes the use of a fossil fuel. It is used as a liquid fuel and is sourced from distillation of heavy oil. This exchange provides the service of operating a water pump with a diesel engine with 1 MJ of diesel. With a LHV of appoximately 42.8 MJ/kg, this equals to 0.0234 kg diesel. The services  includes (air) emissions, the production and provision of fuel and the water pump.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'water pump operation, diesel',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of  water pump operation, diesel', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
